From: HyprWM Fedora maintainers
Subject: [PATCH] build: use Fedora flags and fix public pkg-config dependency

The public C and C++ headers include cairo/cairo.h, so consumers need Cairo's
include flags. Fedora also supplies the optimization flags.

--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -46,7 +46,6 @@
   message(STATUS "Configuring hyprcursor in Debug")
   add_compile_definitions(HYPRLAND_DEBUG)
 else()
-  add_compile_options(-O3)
   message(STATUS "Configuring hyprcursor in Release")
 endif()
 
--- a/hyprcursor.pc.in
+++ b/hyprcursor.pc.in
@@ -6,5 +6,6 @@
 URL: https://github.com/hyprwm/hyprcursor
 Description: A library and toolkit for the Hyprland cursor format
 Version: @HYPRCURSOR_VERSION@
+Requires: cairo
 Cflags: -I${includedir}
 Libs: -L${libdir} -lhyprcursor
